column5: Thanks Jim...it's waitin for me just like that, ready to drop the drawbridge and start the season. Well at least it better still be there....  "excited"? Can't remember when I got a full nights sleep last...need a switch on the brain!
I just heard a bunch of docks were seen floating away up that way
Now that's just mean......

Well nobody else can claim it. We know it's the only diagonally decked dock on the lake, thanks to the gal that boats the Hydro Meter reader around to every place on the lake. I'll find it Terry I'll find it.
news Flash  someone hooked onto it and towed it away
That's hilarious!!
well they tell me the dock is to big for that  plane but a beaver could get rid of it I don't know what they mean but here goes
You're killing me Bud...don't you have real work to do?
if they want me to do more work..they need to pay me more....LOL   I hope they don't read this
I am sitting here at my desk laughing out loud!! What a great way to spend my break!  Thanks Guys... that was just too funny!  Now I have to share it with the whole office...  Cheers,  Jen
I'm going fishing there on Monday for a "few" days. Anyone want to share any hot spots, GPS coordinates or such for Pike?  THANKS!
Into the pepsi a little heavy today Wayne  No get in yer truck and drive,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,just drive and dont look back.
I caught a pike off a dock in Temagami,cant remember exactly where it was but I'm pretty sure the dock was made outta wood. If ya see it make a cast and hold on!!!!
That'd be down around the hub of the lake...THANKS Terry! LOL
yeah I just went to the map and picked a spot but you never know.......lol
Wayne, try this spot but to anyone that you visited the spot.  N44 48.146 W79 55.718
well if he runs there from Temagami it's a long way but he will be able to check up on his place on the way..doesn't seem to be on the lake though must be more grass pike
Calamari?.. care to field this question???
from the pictures i've seen, i'd bet there's great places in eyesight of your dock, you just gotta get out there and try
I don't have to leave the dock wj...my best fish have been caught off of it. Was just adding some humor to the recent Bull around here....and Dawg...we've had this conversation before... lol
Wayne,  Try this general area, last I heard they were banging away...  N47 03.399 W79 49.528
What's that...the coords for the bedroom you slept in or the one beside it? LOL
Mind taking a picture of your dock and pm'ing it to me ???  ???    Cheers,  Jen
I have no issues with public disclosure! lol

Try that one rock, near the small weed bed, by the drop off, close to the sandy shore, beside the gravel bottom with the slow current eddy and timber pile to the left of the creek mouth.  I herd it is a great spot.
Way to funny Wayne!  Whopper

Hey I think I know where those shoes are.. lets not show too much detail in your photos...people will know where all the good spots are   so I'm looking for a spot with shoes and a tire at the dock....this should be easy
Love this picture!  Glad to see you had the drawbridge put in for that family of ducks that like to use this as a short cut.
Terry, does it look familiar now? I thought for sure that you or way would have figured this one out!  Map link
I knew where it was....lol

Wayne  with that new boat and plan e you should be able to reach just about anywhere around Temagami now  Spitzig lake (just off spawning bay) is just full of pike - loads of 4-8 lb fish and the far north end bay is loaded in the spring  Far end of spawning bay is good in the grass flat just in front of the river that flows out of spawning lake.  both shorelines in kokoko bay for 500 yrds past the last A frame cottage.  and of course there's always the very far end of Shining wood bay. As you near the far end there is an island. Start on the north side of the island and troll back west out of the bay for 300 yrds. TRurn arouind and go back.
I dont need to move in...I live right around the corner cast away! They give me day passes.  Thanks Paul...can't fish spawning or kokoko for another week.
Love that shot of the dock Wayne, very nice.  You must be really excited to get up there.  Jim
